2. Verse translations
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The following translations are bundled in `data/translations.json` for
display alongside the Syriac text:

  English: World English Bible (WEB) — public domain
  Spanish: Reina-Valera 1909 — public domain
  Arabic:  Smith & Van Dyke (SVD), 1865 — public domain
  Hebrew:  Modern Hebrew translation; please consult upstream source
           for redistribution terms before reusing this dataset.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Reference lexicons
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The Hebrew and Arabic cognate glosses draw on the following standard
public-domain lexicons. No text is reproduced verbatim from these
works in this repository; only short glosses are derived. See the
methodology page for detail.

  Syriac:  Payne Smith, R. (1903). A Compendious Syriac Dictionary.
  Hebrew:  Brown, F., Driver, S. R., & Briggs, C. A. (1906). BDB
           Hebrew Lexicon. Public domain.
  Arabic:  Lane, E. W. (1863). Arabic-English Lexicon. Public domain.

For currently maintained alternatives, scholars may also wish to
consult HALOT (Koehler-Baumgartner) for Hebrew and Wehr / Lisan
al-Arab for Arabic; those works are still in copyright and are not
used in this project.

